==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spectre
<hw>Spec"tre</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>spectre</ets>, fr. L. <ets>spectrum</ets> an
appearance, image, specter, fr. <ets>specere</ets> to look. See
<er>Spy</er>, and cf. <er>Spectrum</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Something preternaturally visible; an apparition; a ghost; a
phantom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The ghosts of traitors from the bridge descend,⟦br⟧
With bold fanatic <qex>specters</qex> to rejoice.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The tarsius.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A stick insect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Specter bat</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any
phyllostome bat.</cd> -- <col><b>Specter candle</b></col>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a belemnite.</cd> -- <col><b>Specter
shrimp</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a skeleton shrimp. See under
<er>Skeleton</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spectioneer</ent>⟦br⟧

